com.appboy

Interface IAppboyNavigator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AppboyNavigator

    public interface IAppboyNavigator
    This class defines the actions that should be taken when Appboy attempts to display the news feed or open a URI.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void gotoNewsFeed(android.content.Context context, android.os.Bundle extras)
      This delegate method will be called when Appboy wants to display the news feed.
      void gotoURI(android.content.Context context, android.net.Uri uri, android.os.Bundle extras)
      This delegate method will be called when Appboy wants to navigate to a particular URI.

    • Method Detail

      • gotoNewsFeed

        void gotoNewsFeed(android.content.Context context,
                android.os.Bundle extras)
        This delegate method will be called when Appboy wants to display the news feed. If an IAppboyNavigator is set, this method will be called instead of opening a modal news feed.

        This method should implement the necessary logic to navigate to the to the Appboy news feed that is integrated into the app.
        Parameters:
        context - The current context.
        extras - An extras bundle.

      • gotoURI

        void gotoURI(android.content.Context context,
           android.net.Uri uri,
           android.os.Bundle extras)
        This delegate method will be called when Appboy wants to navigate to a particular URI. If an IAppboyNavigator is set, this method will be called instead of the default method (which is defined in com.appboy.ui.AppboyNavigator.
        Parameters:
        context - The current context.
        uri - The Uri to navigate to.
        extras - An extras bundle.
